Detection limit and linear range are two crucial analytical factors of the developed sensors. In this step, these two analytical factors were calculated for monitoring daunorubicin at the surface of 1M3OICl/SnO2-NDGQD/CPE by the SWV method. A linear relation in the concentration range of 0.001–280 μM with a detection limit of 0.40 nM was calculated for sensing daunorubicin using 1M3OICl/SnO2-NDGQD/CPE as an analytical tool (Fig. 9
                        ). The linear dynamic range and limit of detection of 1M3OICl/SnO2-NDGQD/CPE for monitoring of daunorubicin is comparable and in some cases better than previous suggested electrochemical sensors for determination daunorubicin (see Table 2
                        ).
